Hello! In this simple tutorial, you will learn how to install Canopy (https://www.enthought.com/products/canopy/) - a python analysis environment developed by Enthought (https://www.enthought.com/). It is a platform commonly used worldwide and highly recommended by our team. Canopy can be used to easily develop and test python codes, to analyze and visualize data, besides providing simple installation for several different tool packages. Total average installation time is 20 to 40 minutes.
To start using Canopy, follow the steps below:
1.	Access the Canopy download link (https://store.enthought.com/downloads/#default) and select your operational system. After that, click in “Download Canopy Express”.
<html> <img src="https://github.com/thmosqueiro/modeligem/blob/master/extras/installing_canopy/fig1.png"> </html>
The average download time for a 2 Mbps connection speed is 2-3 minutes, depending on the operational system.
2.	Double-click the downloaded file and the installation wizard will be launched. Click on “Next” and follow the instructions provided on the screen. Don’t worry, it’s very simple! 
https://github.com/thmosqueiro/modeligem/blob/master/extras/installing_canopy/fig2.png
3.	Wait until all the installation processes have been performed. This may take several minutes, be patient :)
https://github.com/thmosqueiro/modeligem/blob/master/extras/installing_canopy/fig3.png
4.	After the process has been completed, click on “Finish”.
https://github.com/thmosqueiro/modeligem/blob/master/extras/installing_canopy/fig4.png
5.	Next, choose a directory for your Canopy files and click on “Continue”. 
https://github.com/thmosqueiro/modeligem/blob/master/extras/installing_canopy/fig5.png
6.	Wait until the software has been set up. 
https://github.com/thmosqueiro/modeligem/blob/master/extras/installing_canopy/fig6.png
7.	Start Using Canopy!
https://github.com/thmosqueiro/modeligem/blob/master/extras/installing_canopy/fig7.png
From the main Canopy screen you can access useful tools, such as:
-Python Editor, where you can develop and test codes.
https://github.com/thmosqueiro/modeligem/blob/master/extras/installing_canopy/fig8.png
-Package Manager, where you can download new tools and manage existing packages.
https://github.com/thmosqueiro/modeligem/blob/master/extras/installing_canopy/fig9.png
-Doc Browser, where you can access Canopy and Python guides and online support.
https://github.com/thmosqueiro/modeligem/blob/master/extras/installing_canopy/fig10.png
-Training on Demand, a platform developed by Enthought containing video lectures, exercises and code samples for you to improve your python abilities! 
https://github.com/thmosqueiro/modeligem/blob/master/extras/installing_canopy/fig11.png
8.	Now you are all set to use and explore Canopy! If you need Python assistance, make sure to check our beginners tutorial in the following link (http://nbviewer.ipython.org/github/thmosqueiro/modeligem/blob/master/notebooks/Python_Intro.ipynb)



